Lack of interannotator agreement presents a significant problem in annotation efforts (see, e.g., Marcus et al.1993). With the OntoSem semiautomated approach, there is far less possibility of 73 interannotator disagreement since people only correct the output of the analyzer, which is responsible for consistent and correct deployment of the large and complex static resources: if the knowledge bases are held constant, the analyzer will produce the same output every time, ensuring reproducibility of the annotation.
