Post-editing of automatic annotation has been pursued in various projects (e.g., Brants 2000, and Marcus et al.1993). The latter group did an experiment early on in which they found that “manual tagging took about twice as long as correcting [automated tagging], with about twice the interannotator disagreement rate and an error rate that was about 50% higher” (Marcus et al.1993). This conclusion supports the pursuit of automated tagging methods.
